postcontent: DPMS AAC Recon(heavy barrel) – IMACULATE CONDITION, needs BCG.  So, I bought this gun at Uncle Sam’s few years back for $1,150.  Brought it home, took it to the range, and it wouldn’t cycle.  Having left my tools at home, I just manually cycled the gun for EXACLTY 20 ROUNDS OF MATCH AMMO to get a feel for the HBAR’s groupings, then played with the few other guns we had brought out there that day.  When I took it home, I saw that the gas block was seated (by DPMS, this was a brand new gun) just a hair to the side.  I had a match grade 300BLK project that was almost complete that I was building at the same time, and figured that instead of waiting for the parts, I went ahead and stripped a few of the lower parts and BCG from the Recon and tossed it in the safe.  It still needs the gas block to be aligned to function in semi, and a BCG($80-120), but I picked up the other lower parts and installed them in the gun just last night, so the rest is GTG!  If the buyer wants, I’ll center the gas block for an extra $20, other wise, it’s a pretty easy fix.  This gun is a STEAL @ $525 O.B.O!!!
